Text.SourceString: Oh, <PlayerName>$player</>? As in <PlayerName>$player</> <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=happy>It’s nice to finally meet you!
Farmer? Cool.//I’m one of the doctors here.
I’m starting to worry about that recycling center near the park.//Should I stop taking stuff there?
I don’t know if you’ve noticed, but it looks like it’s overflowing.
I’m starting to worry about that recycling center near the park.//Should I stop taking stuff there?
I don’t know if you’ve noticed, but it looks like it’s overflowing.
There are empty sites here we can repurpose.
Mr. Mayor thought a community garden would make a great space for outdoor activities.//As a doctor, I agree it’s a great idea.//<portrait=happy>It’ll give people another reason to move their bodies.
There are empty sites here we can repurpose.
Mr. Mayor thought a community garden would make a great space for outdoor activities.//As a doctor, I agree it’s a great idea.//<portrait=happy>It’ll give people another reason to move their bodies.

Mr. Mayor thought a community garden would make a great space for outdoor activities.//As a doctor, I agree it’s a great idea.//<portrait=happy>It’ll give people another reason to move their bodies.
I can see how facilities like a recycling center or a community garden could be good for us.//<portrait=annoyed>But I don’t know about upgrading other buildings.
I like how some of the buildings here are old. Like the mansion or the lighthouse.//They feel like a time capsule, you know?
I can see how facilities like a recycling center or a community garden could be good for us.//<portrait=annoyed>But I don’t know about upgrading other buildings.
I like how some of the buildings here are old. Like the mansion or the lighthouse.//They feel like a time capsule, you know?

I average around fourish hours a day at work…//I usually work from 10 am to 2 pm, seeing patients, reviewing medical histories, or doing inventory.//<NPCName>Charles</> runs the reception most of the time.
If I had to choose…//My favorite part of the job is creating care plans with patients.
I’m used to high-stress situations.//I feel like that’s when my knowledge and training really kick in.
It sounds horrible, but the adrenaline rush is addictive.
Paying attention to what you eat is a great way to stay healthy in the long run.//Prevention is worth more than any cure.
Make sure to include fresh vegetables in your diet.//They’re a great source of fiber and nutrients.
It would also make my job a whole lot easier! Heh, heh.
I get all my groceries at Sam’s.//I love how he buys from local sources.
The bad thing about Sam’s is you can’t really find off-season items.
Just holler whenever you have questions about medicine or health.//I know people get nervous about little things like moles or rashes sometimes.
Let me help by giving you peace of mind.
Being in the sun is fine as long as you remember to wear sunscreen.
Oh, another thing!//<portrait=normal>Remember to reapply sunscreen every few hours. That part’s important, and people always forget.
Playing pool after work is a great way to make new friends.//<portrait=normal>But to be frank, I do it mostly because I think I’m pretty good at it.//<portrait=happy>It feels good to win, heh, heh.
I should wear regular clothes more.//<portrait=normal>I’m too lazy to change after my shift, so I just go around in scrubs.
I notice people here love fishing.//I’m all for it, because I think it’s important to unwind.
Yeah! Fishing totally teaches patience.
Chess is all about planning and strategy, just like health.//Well, for me, anyway.
Heh, heh… You got me!//<portrait=normal>I do always find a way to bring the conversation back to health talk.
I don’t usually work on Fridays unless I have an appointment.//Or if there’s an emergency or something.
I’m not too worried about it. The clinic’s usually very quiet.//<NPCName>Charles</> will do just fine on his own.
How’s your week been so far?
I think I might need to go to Sam’s tomorrow.
We sell medicines and vitamins at the clinic.//They can quickly restore your health, so keep some in your backpack just in case.
Useful for an active person like you, no?
I get all my groceries at Sam’s.//I love how he buys from local sources.
The bad thing about Sam’s is you can’t really find off-season items.
I’m not a very good cook, but I try to eat homemade food when I can.//It’s better for you.
I still eat out quite a bit, though! Heh, heh… Old habits die hard, huh?
My tattoos?//<portrait=normal>I got most of them at places I was dispatched to. My experiences in the universal doctor program will stay with me forever.//They’re part of me, just like these tattoos.
Ready for Monday, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Make sure to drink enough water, okay?//Our bodies need it.
It’s so easy to get carried away and forget to listen to our bodies.//I’m guilty of that too.
Ugh… Fashion is hard.
I tried “fashion,” or whatever, back in med school.//Let’s just say I’m glad social media wasn’t big back then.
I don’t need any reminders of my med school days.//Though I do have some old pictures in a box somewhere.//<portrait=happy>Maybe I’ll show you someday.
Who knows…
One of the things I find most challenging about being a doctor is sometimes patients lie.//<portrait=normal>While it’s harmless in most cases, it’s always best to be honest with your doctor.
It’s important for doctors to know your complete medical history to give you the best care possible.
That’s an idea. Yeah, I should probably wear my coat like <NPCName>Charles</>.//<portrait=normal>He looks sleek in that coat, doesn’t he?
But it’s just so hot and restricting.//Can’t run in it either, ’cause it flaps around.
I’m so used to being in scrubs. It feels weird to wear anything else. Other clothes feel restricting, you know?
I DO like green!//<portrait=happy>Can you really tell? Ha!
I like the simple life…//As long as there’s a hot meal on the table, it counts as a good day.
I’m not good at volleyball yet, but I won’t say no if somebody asks me to play.
When I was younger, I worked for the universal doctor program all around the world.//It’s a program that sends medical professionals to foreign places to provide medical assistance.
The pay wasn’t good, but you get one heck of a lot of experience. Plus the satisfaction of helping people in need.
Besides, foreign travel opens your mind, and you develop a thick skin.
One of the things I find most challenging about being a doctor is sometimes patients lie.//<portrait=normal>While it’s harmless in most cases, it’s always best to be honest with your doctor.
It’s important for doctors to know your complete medical history to give you the best care possible.
As a farmer, you must get a lot of daily exercise, yeah?
A pet? Hmm… <NPCName>Millie</> has a lizard that only comes out of hiding when she’s home.//<portrait=annoyed>Does that count?
I’m not sure if it’s male or female. All I know is she calls the lizard Tin.
When I was younger, I worked for the universal doctor program all around the world.//It’s a program that sends medical professionals to foreign places to provide medical assistance.
The pay wasn’t good, but you get a heck of a lot of experience. Plus the satisfaction of helping people in need.
Besides, foreign travel opens your mind, and you develop a thick skin.
Ugh… Fashion is hard.
I tried “fashion,” or whatever, back in med school.//Let’s just say I’m glad social media wasn’t big back then.
I try my best to lead a healthy life, but some days are harder than others.
The plan is to spend the day relaxing and taking things slow.//What about you?
Can’t wear just anything on a workday, though.//I need to wear clothing that lets me move quickly in case of an emergency.
I’m not too picky. As long as it’s comfy, I’m game.
Do you like to hang out at the Local Tavern, <PlayerName>$player</>? I usually go on the weekend when there’s live music.
That <NPCName>Theo</> is really something, isn’t he?
Easier said than done, for sure. It’s not easy for me to find someone I want to spend my life with.
It’s true I never really thought about settling down and having a family, because I’ve always been busy.//But truth be told, long-term commitment scares me.
I don’t have work tomorrow. You, on the other hand, have work every day, huh?
If you need anything from the clinic, <NPCName>Charles</> should be in.
Maybe tomorrow is the day I finally go grocery shopping… Who knows, right?
Don’t count on it, though.
Easier said than done, for sure. It’s not easy for me to find someone I want to spend my life with.
It’s true I never really thought about settling down and having a family, because I’ve always been busy.//But truth be told, long-term commitment scares me.
Not all my tattoos have a meaning behind them…
Not everything has to have a deep meaning. Sometimes you just have to go with your gut.
My hair’s been green for so long. If you asked me what my real hair color is, I wouldn’t know how to answer.
You’ve seen me where?!
I don’t want to scare you, but I don’t think that was me.//I don’t go to the forest.
Easier said than done, for sure. It’s not easy for me to find someone I want to spend my life with.
It’s true I never really thought about settling down and having a family, because I’ve always been busy.//But truth be told, long-term commitment scares me.
You’ve seen me where?!
I don’t want to scare you, but I don’t think that was me.//I don’t go to the forest.
Here’s a nonmedical tip for you. Eat your food in one sitting so it doesn’t go stale.
That’s funny, isn’t it? The food here doesn’t seem to spoil.
<NPCName>Charles</> has to take his antihistamine…//I don’t know what else to tell him. It will literally make him feel better.
Gotta say, not really a big fan of Spring. It’s just not for me.
We do our restocking every Spring… Makes it easier to remember.//Spring…restocking. See?
Have you had your flu vaccine yet?//I recommend getting it every year. If the strain is different, you’ll still be protected.
People usually get their flu vaccines in Winter or Spring. That’s when you’re most vulnerable.//I get mine in Fall to prepare for the coming season. Give it a try, see how it feels.
The Cherry Blossom Festival was really nice, wasn’t it?//<portrait=normal>I had a lot of fun.
Don’t worry about <NPCName>Charles</>. He’s in good hands.//Let me do the worrying for both of us…
Are you sweating as much as I am? Phew!
It’s so hot, <PlayerName>$player</>.//It takes me back to my days volunteering in the doctor program.
Good thing I’m wearing this, huh?//In this heat, a full-blown doctor’s coat… Nu-uh!
Wearing loose clothing is the way to go.//Gotta give your body room to breathe… Not sandals, though.//<portrait=happy>I can’t run in those.

<NPCName>Charles</> and I always prepare for medical emergencies at the Beach Cleanup Festival… Nothing in particular.//It’s good to have doctors around at big gatherings in case someone gets heatstroke or something like that.
Will you be entering the swimming contest?
I think <NPCName>Sunny</> is going to win. He’s got some stamina… Very fast swimmer.
I got this small handheld fan… Oh, so good.//<portrait=normal>Fully automated, battery operated, and all that. You can take it with you in your pocket. The perfect Summer toy.
I had one, anyway… I don’t have the fan anymore.//Accidentally stepped on it. And nobody sells them here.
We have so many melons at home. I think Millie might have gone a little overboard…
Finally, the perfect weather for eating curry.//Curry in Summer is fine, of course, but the heat from inside and out can be too much sometimes.
I’m so glad the air’s cooled down.
What is it they say about Fall? Sweater weather?//<portrait=normal>Yeah, I think that’s right.
I’ve heard only certain animals come out in Fall, but I’m no animal expert.//<portrait=happy><NPCName>Millie</> probably knows way more than I do.
Are you going to show your crops at the Harvest Festival?//<portrait=happy>I love seeing everyone’s hard work.
I think I’ll have curry for dinner today. Seems like the right weather for it.
When I was traveling around the world, most of the places I was dispatched to were really hot.//<portrait=happy>I gotta say, it’s so nice to finally stay put somewhere with Winter.
Do you ever realize how lucky we are to have Winter? I’d rather put on a bunch of layers when it’s cold than constantly be sweating in the heat.
Winter is usually our busiest season. People tend to get sick…which is why I prefer to get my flu vaccination in Fall.//To prepare for this.
We’re stocked up with a lot of cold medicine this season.//The weather is dry and cold… Exactly how viruses like it.
Here we go. It’s Winter. I need to make sure I stay healthy all season.
Finally, the perfect weather for curry. Now <Italic>this</> is what Winter is all about.
I heard about Pufferfish Corp moving in…//<portrait=annoyed>It’s too bad, huh?
The islanders aren’t too happy about it either.
The other day, I was at the store looking for some curly kale for my midday snack, but <NPCName>Sam</> didn’t have any.
Maybe it isn’t kale season anymore.
You can get tulips, wasabi, and celery this time of year.//<portrait=annoyed>Hmm… What else?
Hang on… Not celery! I don’t think it’s celery season yet. Is that right?
Do you like to hang out at Fishensips, <PlayerName>$player</>?//I usually go on the weekend to listen to live music.
Spring literally just arrived, and it feels like <NPCName>Charles</> has spent hours sneezing his nose off.//<portrait=happy>I have to admit, I worry about him.
I took a walk by the lake the other day and saw so many colorful flowers.//What a season!
I try my best to lead a healthy life, but some days are harder than others.
There are so many coconuts at the beach this time of year.
We’re cleaning up the beach soon.
Good thing the beach cleanup starts at 11 am.//<portrait=happy>It gives me a bit of time in the morning to stop by the clinic and pick up some stuff.
If you like mushrooms, black trumpets and matsutakes are currently sprouting near the mayor’s house.
<NPCName>Dinda</> told me.//She goes there a lot, and she has an eye for foraging.
<NPCName>Millie</> has a lizard that only comes out of hiding when she’s home.//<portrait=happy>Cute little thing.
She named the lizard Tin. What a fun name…
I didn’t get to sleep until 3 am, and now I’m absolutely drained.//<portrait=concerned>Humph. I need to stop doing this to myself.
I had some things on my mind. Hard to shake off sometimes.
With the weather getting colder, I see fewer and fewer people outside.//<portrait=annoyed>Do you notice that too?
Oh gosh, piping hot curry would be perfect right now.
I’m not going to tell you how to live your life, but please wash your hands often. Just think about how many things we touch all day.//<portrait=annoyed>Who knows what kind of germs are on our hands?
I thought I’d have more time to read this Winter, but right now I’m more swamped than ever.
I didn’t get to sleep until 3 am, and now I’m absolutely drained.
I had some things on my mind. Hard to shake off sometimes.
Oh gosh, piping hot curry would be perfect right now.
The rain doesn’t change anything, I think…//<portrait=annoyed>But it does slow life down a little.
But it must be convenient for farmers like you…//<portrait=annoyed>A bit? You don’t have to water your plants today, do you?
I wish I could have slept in today. It’s the perfect weather for waking up late and going to bed early.
No Tavern today. I have a lot of chores to do.
I wish I could have slept in today. It’s the perfect weather for waking up late and going to bed early.
No Tavern today. I have a lot of chores to do.
The rain doesn’t change anything, I think…//<portrait=annoyed>But it does slow life down a little.
But it must be convenient for farmers like you…//<portrait=annoyed>A bit? You don’t have to water your plants today, do you?
I’m trying to get more people to go out and garden.//It’s an easy way to get daily exercise.
Oh gosh, piping hot curry would be perfect right now.
Oh gosh, piping hot curry would be perfect right now.
Is it snowing again or something?
You’d think it would’ve stopped by now.
I could use one of those thick knitted blankets right now. Humph…
I’ve learned a lot from <NPCName>Ling</>. She’s very knowledgeable about coral reefs and this island.
I think she’s lived here a long time, but I don’t really know how long.
I love coming here after work and just reading medical journals until the sun sets.
I’m subscribed to four journals, and I’ve been published in a handful.//Mostly articles about interesting cases I encountered abroad.
Sometimes quiet is exactly what we need, isn’t it?
A little health tip: Take vitamins with you when you go out hunting or chopping wood in the forest.//They can boost your health quickly so you can avoid an emergency trip to the clinic.
Even though we’re closed on Sundays, <NPCName>Charles</> and I are always on call in case of an emergency. So don’t worry, okay?
I like my scrubs. They’re comfortable and easy to clean.//But I should wear my white coat once in a while…//<portrait=happy>Change things up a bit.
You know, like <NPCName>Charles</>. He looks good in his coat.
<NPCName>Charles</> is one of the most knowledgeable medical doctors I’ve ever met.//You’re in good hands here.
Free books excite me. Is that sad?
<NPCName>Charles</> and I can subscribe to as many medical journals as we want. The town covers the cost.
It’s very generous of them.
Whenever I can, basically. Dancing is an instant mood-booster.//<portrait=happy>Hey, we should go dancing together sometime.
I’m not a good dancer, but as long as I don’t hurt anyone, and it makes me feel good, who really cares?
I may have had one too many cups of punch. I’m going to call it a night.
I was going to practice some volleyball earlier, but there was nobody outside.//So I decided to chill here instead.
Wah… I’m craving seafood today.//Let’s see what <NPCName>Jim</> is cooking up.
Phew! The sun is a bit strong, isn’t it?//I think I’ll enjoy the beach from inside here.
Nice to see you here, <PlayerName>$player</>!//<portrait=happy>Are you buying or selling?
The radishes here are incredibly crunchy and great for pickling.
The radishes here are incredibly crunchy and great for pickling.
The eggplants here make incredible pickles.
The eggplants here make incredible pickles.
I don’t really go to the forest.//I suppose where I live in Garden Lane is foresty enough for me.
What am I going to do there, anyway?//It’s not like I could just start mining or something.
I should go to Sam’s and pick up a few things. There was basically nothing in the fridge this morning.
I had an apple for breakfast. What about you?//<portrait=happy>I thought we had nothing at home until I found a couple of apples from who knows when. Oh well… Tasted fine.
I should go to Sam’s and pick up a few things. There was basically nothing in the fridge this morning.
I had an apple for breakfast. What about you?//<portrait=happy>I thought we had nothing at home until I found a couple of apples from who knows when. Oh well… Tasted fine.
I think I got a bit too much sun at the beach yesterday.
I don’t know what it is about me, but no matter what time I fall asleep, I always wake up at 6 am.
Oh! You too? What a fun coincidence.//<portrait=normal>It’s weird ’cause it’s literally Winter. I expect my body to sleep in longer.
Don’t overwork yourself, <PlayerName>$player</>. I don’t wanna see you in the clinic.//The heat can be exhausting. I’d be extra careful if I were you.
I do like to see you around, though. Maybe I can challenge you to a game of pool sometime.//<portrait=happy>I bet you’re a good pool player.
I guess I don’t really know if I’m an animal person or not. I’ve never had a pet in my life.
I feel like I’m missing out on something here.
When I actually get a pet, I really want to name it Pat.
Oh, no reason. I just like the name Pat.
I love how pet owners are so passionate about what kind of person they are.//<portrait=happy>I want to join the crowd and say things like “I’m a cat person” or “I’m a lizard person.”
The whole thing is just fascinating!
<PlayerName>$player</>! What a pleasant surprise!
By the way… Thank you for being so supportive.//<portrait=normal>I’m glad to have someone like you in my life.
I’ve met a lot of people, and you’re special, <PlayerName>$player</>.
I was just thinking about my job, and you know what’s interesting?//<portrait=annoyed>Wanting to help people and actually doing the job are two completely different things.
The wild thing about living near the river is the constant fear of flooding every time it rains a little.
The good news is <NPCName>Millie’s</> house doesn’t have a rat problem.//I’m not sure if that’s related, but I suppose no rats counts as a win.
Want to play pool with me? I could use a win. Heh, heh!
<NPCName>Luke</> is old news… We’re meant to be just friends.//Nothing more can come of it.
We don’t dance the same dance, if you catch my drift.
<NPCName>Luke</> is old news… We’re meant to be just friends.//Nothing more can come of it. Our basic principles in life are way too different.
I’m occupied with…umm…someone new now.//Besides, I think there’s something about people who work with their hands that’s just so…admirable.
I don’t know what it is about me, but no matter what time I fall asleep, I always wake up at 6 am.
It’s the Summer sun… Yep! It’s because it’s already so bright that early in the morning.
The wild thing about living near the river is the constant fear of flooding every time it storms like this.
The good news is <NPCName>Millie’s</> house doesn’t have a rat problem.//I’m not sure if that’s related, but I suppose no rats counts as a win.
Is that a new shirt?
It looks good. Works well with your…er…hair.//<portrait=normal>Makes you look sharp.

I just need a house with a kitchen and a place to read my journals, and I’m good.//Then I’ll retire and only go to the clinic two days a week.//<portrait=happy>I plan to spend the rest of my week writing medical articles. Pretty good plan, right?
Until I have enough money saved to afford that, I’ll keep working four days a week.
Have you eaten, <PlayerName>$player</>? Please make sure you eat meals on time, okay?//Something healthy to boost your immune system, maybe.
I worry about you…
It wasn’t easy for me to find someone I wanted to spend my whole life with.
A relationship seemed like a big commitment at first, but when you know, you know, right?
You look spiffy today, <PlayerName>$player</>!//<portrait=happy>You could pass as a Winter decoration.
Oh my! I meant you look nice… Nice, nice, nice.//<portrait=happy>You don’t look bad or anything.
I should start spending more time at the house. It feels like such a waste paying all that rent when I’m never home.
<NPCName>Millie’s</> never home. So it gets boring really fast.//<portrait=blushing>Unless you…umm…want to visit me sometime. We’d have the house to ourselves.
Durian has a strong smell. I know some people love it because of that, like <NpcName>Noah</>.//If someone gives me a durian, will I eat it? Yes.
But am I ever going to go out of my way to find one? No.
I heard you like tacos. Is that right?
I heard it from <NPCName>Sunny</>.//Anyway, we should totally check out Emma’s Taco Truck sometime.
I personally love curry. Red and green both.
I don’t mind other food either. I’m not very picky in that department.//<portrait=annoyed>But I have to say, some fruits have a very strong smell. Like durian.
You’re fun to talk to. One of the coolest people I’ve met, for sure.
If you need anything from me, just let me know.//I can’t give you discount at the clinic, though. The vitamins aren’t mine to give. Ha ha!
There’s an empty room in <NPCName>Jack’s</> ranch house, complete with a compact kitchen and a place to relax.
I was going to rent it, but <NPCName>Millie’s</> place was closer to work.//<portrait=happy>Besides, she charges a lot less than <NPCName>Jack</>.
The clinic doesn’t do home visits.//<portrait=annoyed>Well, <NPCName>Charles</> does, actually. I only do it for emergencies.
For you, <PlayerName>$player</>… If you think you might need extra care.//Something for me to…er…look at. I’ll make an exception for you.
I was walking home last night and almost fell into the river. This town could use more lampposts.
After all these years moving around, I’ve never felt accepted like I do here.//It’s a nice feeling.
I’m not going to give up learning to make curry.//One day, I’m going to make the best curry on the island and be the curry master.
<NPCName>Frank</> currently holds the title… He’s a great cook, isn’t he? Humph. Hard to beat.
In a way, we’re kind of alike, <PlayerName>$player</>. I came here looking for some peace of mind and a place to fit in.
I’m glad I did.
It feels weird sometimes calling myself a doctor, because I don’t feel like one deep down.
In my head, I have this idea about doctors being very serious people.//Whatever that means.
I feel so close to you… I can smell you from here.
It’s nice… You smell really nice.
I spent years traveling around and adjusting to new groups of people constantly.//<portrait=happy>It’s nice to keep the same bunch long enough to celebrate more than one birthday with.
I used to think I needed to be on constant alert to get excitement out of life.//But nope. Things are really exciting with you around.
It’s nice to find someone with the same sense of humor and principles…same wavelength and all.
Oh great! Another fake medical report with a “unicorn finger problem for Yoorie.”//<NPCName>Charles</> must be bored again.
<NPCName>Charles</>!!! It’s not funny. <Italic>I am busy.</> //<portrait=happy>Okay… It’s a little funny.
How he finds time for pranks is beyond me.
<NPCName>Betty</> is one of my easy patients. I like working with her.
Oh, trust me. Plenty of folks here are on my “hard patients” list.//But I’m afraid my lips are sealed.
I hardly have time to travel anymore, but I don’t miss it.//To be perfectly frank, I kind of like not moving somewhere new every other season.
Who knew boring could be so much fun?
I just submitted my billing for the week. That felt good.
Doing paperwork isn’t a lot of fun, but it’s necessary.
I’m here to pick up new reading material. I’ve run out already.
Weird smell, you say? Umm… No. I can’t smell anything.//But once, I lived for two years in an abandoned school right next to a dumpster.
So that may have ruined my nose… The rent was free, though.
I felt like I should settle somewhere and build some meaningful relationships after years of jumping from one place to another.//That’s why I came to Coral Island.

Sometimes I envy <NPCName>Dinda</> and <NPCName>Joko</>. They seem to have such a full life.//<portrait=normal>I see them at the tavern dancing sometimes…just enjoying life together, you know?//<portrait=sad>I want that.
I’m fine being alone, but I think I wouldn’t mind having a partner on lonely days like these, you know.
As soon as Summer hits, I’m wearing my bikini all the time.//<portrait=happy>I’m throwing myself at the beach every single day. Can’t wait!
I got this jacket back when I was in Tangi working with the Universal Doctors.//Feel it! Good quality, right? It was really cheap too.
The jacket is really warm. You’d be surprised!
Spring here isn’t cold. No need to wear a thick jacket anymore.//<portrait=happy>I can move faster now!
Spring is when I usually go to medical conferences.//I stopped going in person, though. They’re fun, but I’m kinda too lazy to go when I can just do it online.
The conferences have free activities like scuba diving, tours, wine tastings… Yeah, It was fun.//Well, the ones I used to go to anyway.
I wonder what kind of medical conferences they have planned for this coming Spring… Hmm… I might check it out!
